Function Reference/get post format string « WordPress Codex
-----------

Returns a pretty, translated version of a post format slug. This can be
used anywhere if slug of a post format is provided.

Usage
-----

` <?php $pretty_format = get_post_format_string($slug); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$slug` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*Optional*) slug of the post format.
    Default: 'standard'

\

Changelog
---------

-   Since: [3.1](/Version_3.1 "Version 3.1")

Source File
-----------

`get_post_format_string()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`.

